# Implementation Workflow

## Output Order

1. Brief clarification (problem, expected behavior)
2. Scenario summary (normal flow, edge cases)
3. Implementation
4. **Tests** (unit + E2E per triggers below)
5. **Doc / Example sync** (per triggers below)
6. Key notes + **Sync summary** (mandatory)

## Doc and Test Sync (MANDATORY — hard gate)

**Intent:** A code change is **not complete** until every applicable artifact is updated **or** explicitly marked **N/A** with reason. **Silent omission = violation of project rules.**

This section is **enforceable**: the agent must treat it as a checklist, not guidance.

### Artifacts (what to keep aligned)

| Artifact | Path / pattern |
|----------|------------------|
| Design | `docs/design/` (start at [index.md](docs/design/index.md)); UI tokens: [11-ui-tokens.md](docs/design/11-ui-tokens.md) |
| Requirements (user stories, AC, examples) | [docs/requirements-format.md](docs/requirements-format.md) |
| Impact checklist | [docs/design-change-impact.md](docs/design-change-impact.md) (core flows + combat/log section) |
| Unit (frontend) | `frontend/src/**/*.spec.js` (Vitest) |
| Unit (backend) | `*_test.go` next to Go packages |
| E2E (browser) | `e2e/browser/*.spec.js` (Playwright) |

### Path → artifact triggers (if you edit files in the left column, update or N/A the right)

Use this table **during** the task, not after. If multiple rows apply, satisfy all unless N/A.

| You change | You MUST |
|------------|----------|
| `frontend/src/game/**` (combat, skills, equipment formulas, `damageUtils`, `battleLogFormat`, pacing) | **Vitest**: add/extend specs under `frontend/src/game/**/*.spec.js` for changed behavior. **Design**: at least one of `docs/design/03-combat.md`, `05-skills.md`, `06-equipment.md` if formulas, damage, loot, or affix behavior changed. **requirements-format.md**: any Example/AC that would be factually wrong. **design-change-impact.md** § combat/log if log strings or player-facing formulas change. **E2E**: update/add if combat **log text**, routing, or main-screen battle UI behavior changed; if only pure logic with identical UI strings, state **E2E N/A** (why). |
| `frontend/src/views/**` or shared UI for main/game flow | **Vitest** if logic in components; **E2E** if user-visible flow or assertion-worthy text changed; else **E2E N/A**. **Design** `09-social-ui.md` / `11-ui-tokens.md` if layout or tokens change. |
| `e2e/browser/**` | Keep helpers aligned with `testHelpers.js` / `workflow.mdc` / `e2e-browser.mdc`. |
| `**/*.go` (backend) | **`go test`** for touched packages; update handler tests if API contract changes. **Design** if API behavior is documented. |
| `docs/design/**` or `docs/requirements-format.md` | Cross-refs in [index.md](docs/design/index.md); ensure code still matches or note doc is source of truth. |

### When you MUST update (same change set as the code)

- **Design docs** — Formulas, skills, combat, equipment, UI flows described or implied by `docs/design/`.
- **requirements-format.md** — Examples/AC that would be wrong after the change.
- **Vitest** — Any behavior change in `frontend/src` logic you touched.
- **Go tests** — Any Go behavior you changed.
- **Playwright** — When **path triggers** above require E2E; otherwise **E2E N/A** with one line.

**Core flows** (squad, recruitment, skills, intro, routing): walk [docs/design-change-impact.md](docs/design-change-impact.md) in full for affected sections.

### When explicit N/A is allowed

Skip an artifact only if it **truly does not apply**, and state **`N/A: <one-line reason>`** in the **Sync summary**. Valid examples: dependency-only bump; comment-only; doc-only task; backend-only with no documented API change. **Silent omission is not allowed.**

### Pre-close checklist (mandatory — do not skip)

1. Which rows in **Path → artifact triggers** applied to this task?
2. For each applicable row: updated artifact, or **N/A** with reason?
3. Ran `npm run test` in `frontend/` when `frontend/src` changed? Ran `go test ./...` when Go changed? Ran `npm run e2e` when E2E was required (not N/A)?

### Final response to the user (required)

End with a **Sync summary** using this shape (fill or N/A each line):

- **docs/design**: &lt;files or N/A&gt;
- **docs/requirements-format.md**: &lt;files or N/A&gt;
- **docs/design-change-impact.md**: &lt;sections or N/A&gt;
- **Unit tests**: &lt;files or N/A&gt;
- **E2E**: &lt;files or N/A&gt;
- **Commands run**: &lt;e.g. npm run test PASS; npm run e2e skipped — reason&gt;

**Incomplete task** if: behavior changed but Sync summary is missing, or N/A is missing where a trigger row applied.

**Frontend / UI:** When editing `frontend/**`, follow `ui-design.mdc` (tokens, gold vs accent, tooltips, forms).

**Design / requirements docs:** When editing `docs/design/**`, `docs/requirements-format.md`, or `docs/design-change-impact.md`, follow `docs-sync.mdc` (cross-refs, checklist, alignment with code).

## Prohibited

- Non-ASCII in code
- Skipping tests for core logic
- **Closing a task with code-only changes** when design, requirements examples, or tests should have been updated (see Doc and Test Sync)
- Using `&&` in PowerShell (use `;` instead)
- Overengineering, placeholder logic

## E2E Definition

- E2E = full UI flow through browser to backend
- Location: `e2e/browser/`
- Use Playwright; detailed rules for specs and port setup: `e2e-browser.mdc` (applies when editing `e2e/browser/**`)

## E2E Port Release (Before Running)

Before running `npm run e2e`, release ports 8080 and 5173 and reset DB (full detail in `e2e-browser.mdc`):

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/release-e2e-ports.ps1
```

The `e2e` npm script runs this automatically. The script also clears `test-results` and resets `text-idle.db` for a fresh run. If running e2e manually or ports are in use, run the script first.

## Anti-Hang Execution Mode

To reduce "stuck" behavior during long operations, use this execution style by default:

- Prefer short, single-purpose commands over large command batches
- Run long tasks in background and poll output every 3-5 seconds
- Send a brief progress update at least every 10 seconds during long tasks
- Read only log tail sections (for example, last 100-200 lines), not full large files
- If no new output appears for 30+ seconds, report current status and next action
- If ports are required (for example 8080/5173), verify port state before and after task start
